sql:
SELECT COUNT(article_id) AS author_article_count
FROM articles
WHERE author_id = 1;

external_knowledge:
External knowledge:
- 'most recently published' refers to the article with the latest publish_date;
- 'trending article' refers to the article with is_trending = 1;
- 'most recent view date' refers to the latest view_date in the article_views table;
- 'has garnered attention' refers to articles with at least one view.
